# The release artifact ships the per-OS PyInstaller binaries directly
# at bin/<name>, mirroring the agent-worktree layout. The shell + batch
# wrappers that ticket #37 traced CRLF-mangling to were removed in
# favour of letting the MCP host pick the right file via PATHEXT.
# PyInstaller outputs are detected as binary by content (ELF / PE magic
# bytes); the explicit rules here are belt-and-suspenders documentation
# for build-side tooling that ever stages these paths in a source tree.
bin/project-issues binary
bin/project-issues.exe binary
